    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That seems like a very optimistic way to look at it. But isn't it true that some people argue the \"mitigation\" strategies usually end up being just band-aids, and that the whole policy is still fundamentally just a way to price people out of the city? If the core mechanism of the policy is to make driving more expensive, how can you say that's anything other than a targeted tax on a specific group of people?",
